# Fundamental Duties of Indian Citizens
It shall be the duty of every citizen of India —

1. To abide by the Constitution and respect its ideals and institutions, the National Flag and the National Anthem\
2. To cherish and follow the noble ideals which inspired our national struggle for freedom\
3. To uphold and protect the sovereignty, unity and integrity of India\
4. To defend the country and render national service when called upon to do so\
5. To promote harmony and the spirit of common brotherhood amongst all the people of India transcending religious, linguistic and regional or sectional diversities; to renounce practices derogatory to the dignity of women\
6. To value and preserve the rich heritage of our composite culture\
7. To protect and improve the natural environment including forests, lakes, rivers, wildlife and to have compassion for living creatures\
8. To develop the scientific temper, humanism and the spirit of inquiry and reform;
9. To safeguard public property and to abjure violence\
10. To strive towards excellence in all spheres of individual and collective activity so that the nation constantly rises to higher levels of endeavour and achievement\
11. Who is a parent or guardian, to provide opportunities for education to his child, or as the case may be, ward between the age of six to fourteen years.

## Speech for EVS - Sem 1


Good Morning Everyone,
I chose Odd Even Scheme and Air Pollution in Delhi as my topic for case study.
So before odd even scheme lets talk a little about air pollution - what it is, its causes and impact.\
Air pollution refers to the presence of harmful and excessive quantities of substances like gases, particles and molecules in atmosphere.
And the major contributors of air pollution include industries, agriculture activities luke stubbke burning and transports.
As per a who survey the air quality in Delhi Is worst of any major city in the world causing serious  problems to the people of delhi including lung infection heart diseases and even cancer.

So,
To tackel this the gov of delhi first introduced odd even scheme in jan 2016
It is a car rationaning scheme in which cars with licence plates ending with odd and even number are allowed to _ply_ on alternate day this scheme has received huge debates both for and against it.
Talking about the consequences,
It was successful in increasing the public transport ridership during its implementation but we can not draw any conclusion about its efect on air pollution as the duration of implementation was too short.

This scheme has been criticised for causing inconvenience to rhe commuters as the public transport system is inadequate and often run overcrowded and late during peak hours.

To successfully address the issue gov must focus on improving the pub trans infra and promoting Non motarise trans

And we as a citizen must choose carpooling cycling and pub trans over personal vehicle

Thanks
